					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex with text written in two columns and masoretic notes in upper and lower margins, as well as on the side margins. Main text in Sefardi square script, masoretic text in Sefardi semi-cursive.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>448 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>245</height>
										<width>180/185</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>155</height>
										<width>115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>448 folios (+ 2 unfoliated parchment flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
									<p>Unfoliated blank leaves after folio 12 and 448.
Hebrew foliation from folio 13 starting with alef, that is, 1 until folio 124 (Hebrew folio 113). Hebrew foliation restarts on folio 125.
</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>46 quires: i10 (folios 1-10), ii4 (folios 11-12b), iii-xii10 (folios 13-112), xiii12 (folios 113-124), xiv-xlii10 (folios 125-414), xliii8 (folios 415-422), xliv-10 (folios 423-432), xlveleven (folios 433-443), xlvisix (folios 444-[449]).</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="31">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Masorah magna in two lines of the upper and three lines of the lower margin. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc>
							<summary>Sefardi square script, punctuated, of the 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"><name type="person" role="scribe">Mosheh Aḳrish</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, 1448 or 1498 (folio 429v: date in the colophon has been partially erased and rewritten. Originally it may have been 5258, that is 1498, and not 5208, that is, 1448.)</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>The margin of folios 2v-10r and 430v embodies the Song of Songs, Ruth, Psalms 1-5 and the beginnings of Psalm 89. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Samuel ben ...</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon as a later correction (folio 429v). See comment in the sale catalogue of Bibliotheca Sussexiana, <ref target="Pettigrew_1827"/>, according to which this manuscript &apos;has been taken out of the Vatican by Junot.&apos; </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">The Reverand Theodore Williams of Hendon</name>, c. 1824: his motto Deus alit me (&apos;God sustains me&apos;) above his armorial shield of a fess, 3 crescents, 3 birds, and a bird on top of the shield ([i verso]), and the monogram &apos;TW&apos;, and the motto ([i verso]). </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Red morocco binding with gauffered edges, the arms and motto of <name type="person" role="owner">Theodore Williams</name> on the upper and lower covers.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
